                        n! / r!(n - r)!
                    </div>
                </div>
                <p>
                    where
                    r! is the <a href=3D"https://stattrek.com/statistics/di=
ctionary?definition=3Dfactorial">factorial</a> of r,
                    and (n=E2=88=92r)! is the factorial of (n=E2=88=92r).
